reviewText: OK, the acting is bad.  I have to agree with that. But the movie was fun and I actually enjoyed it. The ladies in the film reminded me of women I have met and known. The instigating girlfriends and the ones that have your back along with the ones that just can't keep their hands off of each other.  So much drama.  It was as if the poor acting in this actually made it more real or as real as reality TV.

I was intrigued by the title after watching the first 5 minutes of the movie I realize this wasn't for me. However I kept watching hoping it would get better it did not! It appears someone took their own camera got a few people after street and asked them if they wanted to be in a movie. No acting required, just show up and be yourself. I wasn't to thrill with the plot as well. I was hoping that the main character will realize how important it is to have a man in her life versus a woman, that's another subject all together. Granted it was a low very low budget however, I think the writers, producers, and executives could have found a better script than the one they used.

I understand that perhaps the budget for this movie was low. However,  I'm sure they could have gotten much better actors and the story line could have been tighter and much better. Usually part one of a movie is the best but if part 2 follow in this pattern, then just get ready for another flop. I'm glad that this movie was free so I don't have to worry about viewer's remorse.
